By Elliot Smith Immigrants who move there voluntarily and moan that New Zealanders will not adapt to THEIR ways of living. As recent events have shown, the vast majority of Kiwis are very caring and tolerant people, who are very happy to let others practice their own faiths etc. We have no time for hate, and as a multicultural society are willing to engage with you and get to know you. Linguistic and cultural barriers can easily be overcome if both sides make an effort, and most Kiwis like to be hospitable. Source: Quora.